[<p>\u201cThe unauthorized use of <a class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" href="/web/20160723171924/https://twitter.com/hashtag/HereComestheSun?src=hash">#HereComestheSun</a> at the <span class="twitter-hashflag-container"><a class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" href="/web/20160723171924/https://twitter.com/hashtag/RNCinCLE?src=hash">#RNCinCLE</a>\xa0is offensive &amp; against the wishes of the George Harrison estate,\u201d the\xa0Harrison family tweeted.</span></p>, <p dir="ltr" lang="en">The unauthorized use of <a href="/web/20160723171924/https://twitter.com/hashtag/HereComestheSun?src=hash">#HereComestheSun</a> at the <a href="/web/20160723171924/https://twitter.com/hashtag/RNCinCLE?src=hash">#RNCinCLE</a> is offensive &amp; against the wishes of the George Harrison estate.</p>, <p>\u2014 George Harrison (@GeorgeHarrison) <a href="/web/20160723171924/https://twitter.com/GeorgeHarrison/status/756329307325235202">July 22, 2016</a></p>, <p><script async="" charset="utf-8" src="/web/20160723171924js_/http://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js"></script></p>, <p><span class="twitter-hashflag-container">Another tweet added:\xa0\u201cIf it had been Beware of Darkness, then we MAY have approved it! <a class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" href="/web/20160723171924/https://twitter.com/hashtag/TrumpYourself?src=hash">#TrumpYourself</a>.\u201d</span></p>, <p dir="ltr" lang="en">If it had been Beware of Darkness, then we MAY have approved it! <a href="/web/20160723171924/https://twitter.com/hashtag/TrumpYourself?src=hash">#TrumpYourself</a></p>, <p>\u2014 George Harrison (@GeorgeHarrison) <a href="/web/20160723171924/https://twitter.com/GeorgeHarrison/status/756331712058195968">July 22, 2016</a></p>, <p><script async="" charset="utf-8" src="/web/20160723171924js_/http://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js"></script></p>, <p>The song, written by Harrison and released on the 1969 Beatles album <em>Abbey Road</em>, was played over the loudspeakers at the Quicken Loans Arena Thursday night as Ivanka Trump, daughter of Republican presidential nominee Donald Trump, made her way onstage to deliver a speech and introduce her father.</p>, <p>Harrison\u2019s estate were not the only song rights holders\xa0to complain about their music being used during the Republican party\u2019s biggest\xa0political event of the year.</p>, <p>Rocker Paul Rodgers also scolded the RNC\xa0over\xa0the use of his song \u201cAll Right Now,\u201d originally performed by his band Free.</p>, <p>\u201cPermission to use \u2018All Right Now\u2019 was never sought for or granted by me. My lawyer is dealing with this matter. \u2013 Paul,\u201d the English singer tweeted earlier in the week.</p>, <p dir="ltr" lang="en">Permission to use "All Right Now" was never sought for or granted by me. My lawyer is dealing with this matter. \u2013 Paul</p>, <p>\u2014 Paul Rodgers (@_paulrodgers) <a href="/web/20160723171924/https://twitter.com/_paulrodgers/status/755094139650408450">July 18, 2016</a></p>, <p><script async="" charset="utf-8" src="/web/20160723171924js_/http://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js"></script></p>, <p>Earlier in the week, British rock band Queen also complained about the use of the band\u2019s 1977 hit \u201cWe Are the Champions\u201d during a\xa0Trump\xa0convention appearance.</p>, <p>\u201cAn unauthorised use at the Republican Convention against our wishes \u2013 Queen,\u201d the band tweeted on Tuesday.</p>, <p>Queen lead guitarist Brian May doubled down, writing on his <a href="/web/20160723171924/http://brianmay.com/" target="_blank">website</a>:\xa0\u201cMy personal reaction to Donald Trump using our music? We\u2019d never give permission. We are taking advice on what steps we can take to ensure this use does not continue.\u201d</p>, <p>May insisted that it has always been the band\u2019s politics to never \u201callow Queen music to be used as a political campaigning tool.\u201d</p>, <p>\xa0</p>, <p><em>Follow\xa0Jerome Hudson\xa0on Twitter:\xa0<a 